The uses of biometrics are divided into two groups: identification (recognizing one person among others) and authentication (ensuring that the person is the person who claims to be).
The identification concerned the issuance of identity papers: it is necessary to compare the biometric elements (prints, photo, iris) with the information that the State has on all citizens already registered.
This ensures that a person does not attempt to usurp someone else's identity.
