This is the real news about Europe: the grand post-war plan to unify Europe is definitely stalled.
With the euro crisis, the Europe Project has officially died.
Across Europe, parties that oppose the EU or advocate the abandonment of the euro as a common currency are gaining ground.
Even in Germany, the Eurosceptic Alternative for Germany, founded only this year and arrived out of nowhere, won almost five million votes in the September federal election and pulled out the Liberal Democratic Party (equivalent to our Liberal Democrats) in the Bundestag.
